for Compensation (of standby counsel - Court is not requiring reimbursement)
Letter from TC, referring to his plea

Other Adrian Longacre in court as standby counsel for TC. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Toni P. Cayton in court, pro se.  DA Harper states that she and the Defendant have reached an agreement for resolution, calling for def's plea to 3 bail jumping counts for dismissal or dismissal/read-in of remaining counts and cases.  DA states that 15CM115 would be dismissed outright.  15CM127 would be dismissed and read-in.  Counts 1 and 5 of 15CM162 would be dismissed/read in.  Def requests motions decided first before he proceeds with plea agreement.  Def addresses the Court.  Court addresses Def.  Def asks for recess to consider plea waiver questionnaire.  Recess.  Resuming, Def pleads no contest to counts 2, 3, and 4 of 15CM162.  Court's colloquy re pleas.  110 days jail each count, concurrent with each other, with 28 days credit and 1 set of courts; DNA surcharges waived due to def's indigency; no repayment order on standby counsel cost.  All remaining counts and cases are dismissed outright.  Jail stayed until Nov. 2nd between 6-7 a.m.  With huber.  Def to submit DNA sample at the RCSD before leaving the courthouse today.

Status conference at 10-13-2015 03:00 pm

Defendant Toni P. Cayton in court, in custody, without counsel, for motion hearing in 15CM115, 15CM162, and 15CM127. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Def does not have counsel but has requested a jury trial; trial is coming up in November; def wants to continue to represent himself but is asking Court to appoint standby counsel for his upcoming jury trial.  Court recesses so that def can consider waiver of counsel forms for these cases.  After the recess, DA states that she and Def have talked; State has made an offer that may resolve these matters; suggests putting that on the record Oct. 14th at the final status/jury status hearing in these cases.  Def sworn by clerk for questioning by the Court re def's eligibility for standby counsel appointment by the Court.  Court finds def is indigent.  Further, if there's a bill for appointed counsel at the end of the case, Court may not require def to reimburse Richland County.  Court questions def on his desire to represent himself.  Court's colloquy with def re waiver of counsel.  Court finds def is competent to represent himself; required colloquies have been conducted and required findings made per Klessig.  Court appoints Atty. Adrian Longacre as standby counsel.  Clerk calls Atty. Longacre.  2:38 p.m., Atty. Longacre joins the hearing at this point via telephone.  Court asks if Atty. L will accept the Court's appointment as standby counsel.  Atty. L accepts the standby appointment but will need to check his calendar to determine if he's available for jury trial Nov. 9 and 10.  Court states that it will grant a joinder of the cases for the trial; all matters will be tried together.  Court sets additional status for Oct. 13th at 3:00.  The 13th will replace the scheduling on Oct. 14th.  DA requests waiver of right to counsel for the sole, limited purpose of offer exchange from the State.  Court notes that def has already waived his right to attorney and is proceeding pro se, although the standby counsel allows him to have "backup."  
  Status conference scheduled for October 13, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
